# Documentation Discipline

- Documentation updates are mandatory when behavior or structure changes.
- Keep docs synchronized with implementation in the same task.
- Update the correct documentation scope:
  - Architecture changes -> `docs/architecture/`
  - API changes -> `docs/api/*.postman_collection.json` and `postman/collections/DMS API/` (keep both in sync)
  - Module changes -> `docs/modules/` (include endpoint flow details: route entry, middleware chain, handler, service path, and business-logic response branches)
  - Provider changes -> `docs/providers/`
  - Database changes -> `docs/database/` and `docs/database/tables/*.md` (one file per table with columns, types, nullability, defaults, PK/FK, unique/index details)
  - Workflow/process changes -> `docs/workflows/`
- Update `docs/knowledge-base.md` after implementation.
- Use module flow docs and per-table schema docs as first-stop references when tracing function or API flow.
